    "notes": "The example shows a formula element in action and compares it with an equivalent built-in element. **Dioptric Lens** is a custom element whose matrices are calcuated by user-given Python code. It works the same as **Thin Lens** element.\n\nSelect both `F1` and `DL1` elements and use *Element -> Disable\\Enable* command to switch beewen them and recalculate corresponding stability maps. Use *Plot -> Freeze* to keep the other graph visible when its driving element gets disabled.",
